<TITLE> PM gives Tk 2 lakh to each civilian family </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 8 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina Sunday handed Tk 2 lakh in assistance to each of the families of the three civilians killed in the BDR mutiny last month, an aide said. Rickshaw-puller Amzad Ali, vegetable vendor Hridoy Hossain and student Tareq Aziz were killed on the first day of Feb. 25-26 mutiny by renegade BDR men. The prime minister also announced that the family members would be given jobs, her deputy information secretary Mahbubul Hoque Shakil said. The families told Hasina that the local Awami League leaders were keeping in touch with them since the incident. The families of Amzad and Hridoy said AL MP Fazle Noor Tapash gave each family Tk 50000 and the local AL Tk 20000. Tariq's family said the MP for Dhaka-14 constituency Aslamul Haq Aslam had given them Tk 25000. bdn
